===Proper noun===
'''Jerusalem'''
# The capital of [[Israel]]; ancient capital of the Jewish Kingdoms of Israel (established as such by King [[David]]), Judah and Judea, ancient city of Roman, Byzantine, Arab, Ottoman and British Mandate [[Palestine]]; a [[holy]] [[city]] for [[Judaism]] (First Temple built by [[Solomon]], Second Temple and Herodian Temples of Solomon), [[Christianity]] (Christ’s crucifixion and resurrection), and [[Islam]] (Muhammad’s ascension to heaven).

